# Folder Structure

## Monorepo Layout

```
/
├── .cursor/          # AI platform (rules, skills, agents, MCP)
├── apps/
│   ├── api/          # FastAPI backend
│   └── web/          # Next.js storefront
├── docs/             # Platform and project documentation
├── workflows/        # Domain workflow playbooks (catalog, checkout, handoff)
├── templates/        # Document templates
├── openapi.yaml      # API contract (OpenAPI MCP)
├── docker-compose.yml
└── .env.example
```

## Backend (`apps/api/`)

Feature-first under `apps/api/app/features/`:

```
features/
├── catalog/
│   ├── presentation/    # routers
│   ├── application/     # use cases
│   ├── domain/          # entities, aggregates
│   └── infrastructure/  # repositories, adapters
├── checkout/
├── orders/
├── payments/
└── customers/
```

Avoid technology-first folders (`controllers/`, `services/`, `utils/` at root).

## Frontend (`apps/web/`)

Feature-first under `apps/web/src/`:

```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router
├── components/       # shared UI, shadcn in components/ui/
├── features/         # catalog, cart, checkout pages
├── lib/              # api client, utils
└── store/            # Zustand stores
```

## Domain Feature Names

Preferred backend/frontend feature modules:

- catalog
- orders
- checkout
- payments
- search
- customers

Each feature contains logical layers (presentation → application → domain → infrastructure on backend).

Avoid dumping unrelated files into shared folders.

